decks.notes: This deck focuses on utilizing the Greasefang Parhelion combo to create a powerful board presence and overwhelm the opponent. By combining cards like Fleeting Spirit, Monument to Endurance, and Parhelion II, the deck can quickly build a threatening army of creatures. The inclusion of cards like Thoughtseize and Fatal Push allows for disruption of the opponent's strategies, while Sheltered by Ghosts provides protection for key creatures. With careful planning and timing, the deck aims to outpace and outmaneuver the opponent to achieve victory.

This deck focuses on aggressive strategies using Rakdos colors to put pressure on the opponent early in the game. It includes a mix of efficient removal spells like Abrade and Fatal Push to control the board, along with disruptive cards like Thoughtseize and Duress to disrupt the opponent's game plan. Bloodtithe Harvester and Reckoner Bankbuster help to quickly close out games, while cards like Kroxa, Titan of Death's Hunger and Sheoldred, the Apocalypse provide additional value and resilience. The deck aims to quickly overwhelm the opponent and maintain pressure throughout the game.

The deck focuses on quickly overwhelming the opponent with low-cost creatures and burn spells, allowing the player to deal damage efficiently and aggressively. The key strategy revolves around building a board presence with creatures like Monastery Swiftspear and Emberheart Challenger, while also using spells like Reckless Rage and Monstrous Rage to control the board and damage the opponent directly. The deck aims to maintain pressure and aggression throughout the game, never letting the opponent gain control or stabilize.

The deck focuses on using control spells to manage the opponent's board and hand, while also utilizing card advantage through draw spells and powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Hero of Dominaria. The addition of the companion Kaheera, the Orphanguard adds extra value to the deck by providing a powerful creature that can be cast from outside the game. The deck also includes various land cards to fix mana and disrupt the opponent's mana base, ensuring that the control player can maintain control of the game.

The deck focuses on quick and aggressive plays with Arclight Phoenix as the main threat. By utilizing cheap spells, card draw, and ways to bring back Phoenix from the graveyard, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent in the early game. The inclusion of cards like Artist's Talent and Into the Flood Maw provide additional advantage and disruption to control the game tempo. The deck's key strength lies in its ability to consistently bring back Arclight Phoenix and apply pressure on the opponent while maintaining card advantage through various draw spells.

The main focus of this deck is to aggressively apply pressure on the opponent using low-cost creatures like Soul-Scar Mage, Monastery Swiftspear, and Emberheart Challenger, while supporting them with spells like Reckless Rage and Monstrous Rage to control the board. The deck also includes cards like Cori-Steel Cutter and Stormchaser's Talent to further enhance the aggro strategy. Additionally, the deck includes some card advantage and mana fixing with cards like Stock Up and Riverglide Pathway. The mana base is optimized for a quick and consistent mana curve with a mix of dual lands and basic lands.

The deck focuses on utilizing counterspells, board wipes, and card advantage to control the game and out value the opponent. It also includes a companion to provide additional synergy and support. The mana base is built to support a variety of spells and abilities while also including utility lands to help control the board and fix mana. Overall, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while setting up for powerful late game threats and card advantage engines.

The main idea of this UW Control deck is to focus on controlling the game through counterspells, removal, and card advantage. The deck aims to disrupt the opponent's strategy while building up its own resources and eventually winning through powerful planeswalker abilities or by overwhelming the opponent with card advantage. The inclusion of Kaheera as a companion adds an additional threat and synergizes with some of the creature cards in the deck. Overall, the deck is designed to outlast the opponent and secure victory through careful strategy and resource management.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on quickly equipping Colossus Hammer onto creatures like Fervent Champion and Kellan, the Fae-Blooded to deal massive amounts of damage early in the game. The Leyline Axe and Sigarda's Aid provide extra support for equipping the hammer efficiently, while cards like Cloud, Midgar Mercenary and Kazuul's Toll Collector offer additional aggressive threats on the battlefield. The addition of utility cards like Shadowspear and Sheltered by Ghosts helps to keep the pressure on opponents while protecting key creatures.

This Esper Aggro deck focuses on early game aggression and disruption to control the board and disrupt the opponent's strategy. It includes a mix of creatures with evasion and removal spells to clear the way for your attackers. Cards like Fatal Push and Thoughtseize help to keep the opponent on the back foot, while threats like Cecil, Dark Knight and Nashi, Searcher in the Dark put pressure on the opponent's life total. The deck also includes some late-game options like Valki, God of Lies and Kaito, Bane of Nightmares to close out the game if needed.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's hand with cards like Thoughtseize and Duress while putting pressure on them with aggressive creatures like Bloodtithe Harvester and Sheoldred, the Apocalypse. The deck utilizes a mix of removal spells like Fatal Push and Go for the Throat to clear the way for its creatures. The land base is optimized for a fast and efficient mana base, allowing the deck to consistently cast its spells. Overall, the deck aims to apply early pressure while disrupting the opponent's game plan to secure a quick victory.

The main concept of this Rakdos Aggro deck is to disrupt the opponent's hand with cards like Thoughtseize and Duress, while applying pressure with aggressive creatures like Bloodtithe Harvester and Graveyard Trespasser. The deck also aims to control the board with removal spells such as Fatal Push and Go for the Throat. Additionally, the deck utilizes a combination of lands to support its aggressive game plan, including Mutavault and Blightstep Pathway. Overall, the deck focuses on a fast-paced strategy that aims to overwhelm the opponent quickly.

The main concept of this Jeskai Ascendency combo deck is to quickly and efficiently set up Jeskai Ascendancy alongside a variety of spells and creatures that can trigger its abilities. By using cards like Toph, Hardheaded Teacher and Stormchaser's Talent to generate mana and draw cards, while also utilizing cards like Botanical Sanctum and Sylvan Caryatid for mana fixing and ramp, the deck aims to create a powerful engine that can generate a large amount of value and potentially win the game in a single turn.

This deck focuses on utilizing cheap spells and card draw to quickly fill up the graveyard with Arclight Phoenixes, allowing for explosive turns and a quick clock on the opponent. The inclusion of evasion creatures like Picklock Prankster and Ledger Shredder helps to push through damage and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck also includes a few control elements like Lightning Axe and Pyroclasm to deal with threats and protect the board. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with a fast and aggressive game plan.

This deck focuses on using low-cost, aggressive creatures like Soul-Scar Mage, Monastery Swiftspear, and Emberheart Challenger to quickly overwhelm the opponent. It also includes cards like Reckless Rage and Experimental Synthesizer to control the board and deal with threatening creatures. The deck aims to maintain pressure on the opponent while efficiently removing their threats, ultimately securing victory through fast-paced and strategic gameplay. The mana base is designed to support the deck's aggressive playstyle, allowing for consistent casting of spells and creatures.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on quickly establishing a board presence with low-cost creatures like Novice Inspector and Ornithopter, supported by cards like Gleeful Demolition and Venerated Loxodon. By efficiently pumping out creatures and using cards like Cosmogrand Zenith, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with versatile threats and aggressive plays. The addition of cards like Reckless Bushwhacker and Warden of the Inner Sky allows for explosive turns and the ability to quickly close out games before opponents can stabilize. The deck seeks to maintain pressure and tempo throughout the game to secure a swift victory.
